To compile on Linux, just run make
To compile on FreeBSD, run make -f Makefile.FreeBSD

No installation is currently available, (poor) documentation is located at http://mpg123d.stromnet.org/

Place a mpg123d.conf in /etc, /usr/local/etc, or specify other location with -c parameter.


To kill mpg123d, send a SIGINT to it, by either do:

killall -INT mpg123d

or

kill -INT <pidofmpg123d>




